  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Planning Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Job description</p><ul><li>Develop and maintain detailed project schedules using <strong>Primavera P6/MS Project</strong>, ensuring alignment with project objectives</li><li>Monitor progress, identify potential delays, and propose corrective actions to keep the project on track</li><li>Prepare progress reports, dashboards, and presentations for stakeholders</li><li>Coordinate with project teams to assess risks, resource allocation, and critical path activities</li><li>Conduct site visits to verify progress and update schedules accordingly</li><li>Ensure compliance with contractual timelines and project milestones</li><li>Assist in claims management and delay analysis, if required</li><li>Liaise with clients, consultants, and contractors to resolve scheduling conflicts</li><li>Any other adhoc duties as assigned by management</li></ul><p>Job requirements</p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or related field</li><li>Min 5 years of experience as a Planning Engineer, preferably in high-rise residential/commercial projects/LTA projects</li><li>Proficiency in Primavera P6 (Earn Value Analysis), MS Project (with resource and cost loading), and other planning tools</li><li>Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills</li><li>Knowledge of construction methodologies, contracts, and risk management</li><li>Ability to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines</li><li>Near Jurong East Mrt</li></ul>",
